    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.001 Orellana, Manuel/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-17T16:00:00-07:00"
                            >December 17, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. Congress met today in special session and accepted the resignation of
                    Provisional President Palma and appointed General Orellana, <pb facs="0272"
                        n="178" xml:id="pg_178"/> the head of the revolutionary movement, as
                    Provisional President. This appointment is illegal because it is contrary to
                    article 65 of the Constitution and the pacts of 1923.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d134fn2">See <hi rend="italic">Conference on Central American
                            Affairs, Washington, December 4, 1922–February 7, 1923</hi> (Washington,
                        Government Printing Office, 1923), p. 287.</note> Several Deputies have told
                    me that the Congress was surrounded by armed forces and the Deputies were forced
                    by threats to vote for General Orellana.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McCafferty</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
